      • SEGMENT_IDENTIFIER

        public static final int SEGMENT_IDENTIFIER
        A segment is a stream of bytes with length <= 65535.The segment begins with a marker. A marker consists of 2 bytes beginning with 0xFF, and ending with a byte between 0 and 0xFF.

      • TEM

        public static final int TEM
        Define JPEG markers. A marker is prefixed by a SEGMENT_IDENTIFIER. Most markers will have additional information following them. When this is the case, the marker and its associated information is referred to as a "header." In a header the marker is immediately followed by two bytes that indicate the length of the information, in bytes, that the header contains. The two bytes that indicate the length are always included in that count.
